  "body_sections": [
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Returns the discrete, linear convolution of two one-dimensional sequences."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The convolution operator is often seen in signal processing, where it\nmodels the effect of a linear time-invariant system on a signal "
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "[1]_"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ".  In\nprobability theory, the sum of two independent random variables is\ndistributed according to the convolution of their individual\ndistributions."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "If "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "v"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is longer than "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "a"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ", the arrays are swapped before computation."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Extended Summary"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "First one-dimensional input array."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "(N,) array_like",
              "inline": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "First one-dimensional input array."
                }
              ],
              "name": "a",
              "type": "field_list"
            },
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "Second one-dimensional input array."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "(M,) array_like",
              "inline": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "Second one-dimensional input array."
                }
              ],
              "name": "v",
              "type": "field_list"
            },
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "items": [
                    {
                      "blocks": [
                        {
                          "inline": [
                            {
                              "kind": "text",
                              "text": "By default, mode is 'full'.  This returns the convolution\nat each point of overlap, with an output shape of (N+M-1,). At\nthe end-points of the convolution, the signals do not overlap\ncompletely, and boundary effects may be seen."
                            }
                          ],
                          "type": "paragraph"
                        }
                      ],
                      "term_inline": [
                        {
                          "kind": "text",
                          "text": "'full':"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "blocks": [
                        {
                          "inline": [
                            {
                              "kind": "text",
                              "text": "Mode 'same' returns output of length "
                            },
                            {
                              "kind": "code",
                              "text": "max(M, N)"
                            },
                            {
                              "kind": "text",
                              "text": ".  Boundary\neffects are still visible."
                            }
                          ],
                          "type": "paragraph"
                        }
                      ],
                      "term_inline": [
                        {
                          "kind": "text",
                          "text": "'same':"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "blocks": [
                        {
                          "inline": [
                            {
                              "kind": "text",
                              "text": "Mode 'valid' returns output of length\n"
                            },
                            {
                              "kind": "code",
                              "text": "max(M, N) - min(M, N) + 1"
                            },
                            {
                              "kind": "text",
                              "text": ".  The convolution product is only given\nfor points where the signals overlap completely.  Values outside\nthe signal boundary have no effect."
                            }
                          ],
                          "type": "paragraph"
                        }
                      ],
                      "term_inline": [
                        {
                          "kind": "text",
                          "text": "'valid':"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "definition_list"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "{'full', 'valid', 'same'}, optional",
              "inline": [],
              "name": "mode",
              "type": "field_list"
            }
          ],
          "title": "Parameters",
          "type": "field_list"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Parameters"
    },
